On March 9, 2015, the U.S. Food and Drug Administration warned that Varenicline, in the form of Pfizer Inc''s quit-smoking drug, Chantix, has been associated with seizures and that some patients who drink while taking the drug may become aggressive or black out. Pfizer is conducting an additional safety study of the drug, results of which are  expected in late 2015. The FDA said it is keeping the black box in place at least until the results of the trial are announced.', '["N07BA03"]', '[]');
